ncluding the burning of ancient Alexandria's library and contemporary library lootings at the hands of ISIS. With insight and passion, the author underscores the universal centrality of books and their unique importance to a democratic, civilized, and engaged society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 22. Okt 2019) 0aLibraries. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Literary.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300235494423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300235494.jpg  aGBV-deGruyter-alles